properties.areaDesc: James River from Jamestown to the James River Bridge; James River from James River Bridge to Hampton Roads Bridge-Tunnel
properties.headline: Marine Weather Statement issued January 14 at 5:05PM EST by NWS Wakefield VA
properties.description:
Automated weather sensors and web cameras indicate areas of fog
have developed across much of the James River. Visbilities
are generally greater than 1 SM at this time, but may diminish
further as we head through the next couple of hours. A Marine
Dense Fog Advisory may be needed later this evening or overnight.

If you must navigate, exercise caution. Use proper fog signals.
Make sure all running lights are on. Remember to use your radar
and compass.

NWSheadline: AREAS OF MARINE FOG THIS EVENING AND OVERNIGHT
